headlines.description: Omari Spellman had 26 points, 11 rebounds and helped No. 1 Villanova kick off a rousing day in Philadelphia sports with a 92-76 win over Seton Hall on Sunday.
headlines.shortLinkText: No. 1 Villanova tops Seton Hall 92-76, fans chant for Eagles

headlines.description: Keita Bates-Diop scored a career-high 35 points and had 13 rebounds and No. 17 Ohio State held off Illinois 75-67 on Sunday.
headlines.shortLinkText: No. 17 Ohio State holds off pesky Illinois to win 75-67

video.headline: Ohio State wins behind Bates-Diop's big game

headlines.description: Shannon Evans II scored 23 points and Romello White added 21 as No. 25 Arizona State beat Washington State 88-78 on Sunday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Evans leads No. 25 Arizona State over Washington St. 88-78

headlines.description: Ky Bowman scored his only three baskets after halftime in overtime and finished with 17 points to carry Boston College to an 80-72 victory over Georgia Tech on Sunday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Bowman's big OT carries BC past Georgia Tech, 80-72

headlines.description: Deyshonee Much scored 21 points on 7-of-9 shooting from the 3-point line and Iona took control early and cruised to a 98-64 win over Marist on Sunday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Much has 7 3s, 21 points as Iona blows past Marist 98-64

headlines.description: Jordan Swopshire had 16 points, with four 3-pointers, and nine rebounds to help Colgate beat Navy 69-64 on Sunday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Swopshire hits late 3, Colgate beats Navy 69-64

headlines.description: Kendrick Nunn and Jalen Hayes, the nation's top-scoring duo, combined for 46 points to lead Oakland to an 82-74 victory over IUPUI on Sunday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Kunn, Hayes team again to lead Oakland over IUPUI 82-74

headlines.description: Anthony Cowan Jr. scored 23 points, Kevin Huerter added 19 and Maryland squeezed past Wisconsin 68-63 Sunday to stretch the Badgers' losing streak to five games.
headlines.shortLinkText: Maryland uses late surge to beat Wisconsin 68-63

headlines.description: Junior Etou had 17 points and 12 rebounds for his sixth double-double of the season, DaQuan Jeffries added 16 points and Tulsa beat South Florida 63-54 on Sunday for its sixth straight win in the series.
headlines.shortLinkText: Etou's 6th double-double leads Tulsa by South Florida 63-54

headlines.description: Kahil Dukes scored a career-high 37 points to lead Niagara over Monmouth 96-91 on Sunday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Dukes scores career-high 37 in Niagara's 96-91 victory

headlines.description: Stevie Jordan had 18 points and six assists, Dimencio Vaughn added 16 points with four steals and Rider beat Quinnipiac 74-59 on Sunday for its sixth straight victory.
headlines.shortLinkText: Rider beats Quinnipiac 74-59 for 6th straight victory

headlines.description: Nate Pierre-Louis scored 18 points and Shizz Alston Jr. had 15 points and a career-high 10 assists in Temple's 83-76 victory over Tulane on Sunday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Temple follows up win over Shockers by beating Tulane 83-76

nowFeed.headline: Under Sean Miller Deandre Ayton is maximizing his enormous potential. Ayton has always possessed the physical tools and a solid basketball IQ. He has worked hard at Zona along with making the adjustments to college basketball. For a freshman big man it's really hard to dominate right away. Since he arrived in the states he was a top ranked player in his class. Would have been top 5 in last years NBA draft. Now he will be a top 3 pick and will be much more prepared.

nowFeed.headline: Cincinnati's loss at Houston will likely drop them from the No. 2-seed line in Joe Lunardi's Bracketology, with Texas Tech likely being the beneficiary to move up. The Cougars, who were a 10-seed coming into the night, scored another big resume win after picking one up over Wichita State in January.
nowFeed.story: Cincinnati's loss at Houston will likely drop them from the No. 2-seed line in Joe Lunardi's Bracketology, with Texas Tech likely being the beneficiary to move up. The Cougars, who were a 10-seed coming into the night, scored another big resume win after picking one up over Wichita State in January.

nowFeed.headline: Houston upsets No. 5 Cincinnati 67-62, ending the Bearcats nation-leading 16-game winning streak. It's the first time the Cougars have beaten two top-10 opponents in a season since 1984.
nowFeed.story: Houston upsets No. 5 Cincinnati 67-62, ending the Bearcats nation-leading 16-game winning streak. It's the first time the Cougars have beaten two top-10 opponents in a season since 1984.

nowFeed.headline: Ironically, Cincinnati's loss to Houston also finally gives Cincinnati its first win over a likely NCAA Tournament team.
